<br>
So as her horse took the final steps into the village, she glanced around. It must have been.... Well, I don't know, but a really long time since the last time she was there. Emerald greens glanced around the village until they fell on Alysia as she entered the hut. She jumped off from her horse and patted the side, letting it run off, but keeping her eyes on the hut. She walked up and stood next to the entrance after Alysia was finished entering, her eyes straight ahead and her arms folded behind her back. She'd let Yakut be with her best friend right now and give her condolences when the time was appropriate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Platinum Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 1017<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/5/03 8:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Death of an Amazon Princess</span><hr size=1> It was an odd feeling in the pit of Hippolyte's stomach as she road into the valley city.  Just as Yakut had brought her own mother back from the dead, the queen of the Tanais River Valley had lost her daughter to the same.  Hippolyte let her mare lumber thru the main street of the city.  Coming upon Yakut's hut, just as she saw Alysia enter.  <br>
<br>
Hippolyte stopped her mare and just sat back in the saddle.  Seeing Ariah, she quietly nodded.  It was a sad day and not one for speaking.  At least not Hippolyte.  Deciding not to intrude on the Queen's mourning and talk with Alysia, Hippolyte turned her mare back around and backed it's backside near the hut wall.  Like a quiet guardian, Hippolyte sat there on the horse gazing forward.  Waiting for any instructions from Yakut or her attendents as to the needs of the great shaman queen.  And her hand resting on the end of her scimitar, to guard from any who would attempt to try something on Yakut while she mourned.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 453<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/6/03 5:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Death of an Amazon Princess</span><hr size=1> Alysia looked to the other Queens and sadly gave a greeting to them both and completely entered Yakut's hut. She sighed lightly and kneeled down next to Yakut.<br>
<br>
It was a rare occasion when Alysia was seen with great emotion on her face, a show of sadness and condolences. At least in the Nation. Alysia-Samsara was an amazon who tried her best to keep a strong face in front of others, she enjoyed her reputation, and her prideful self . .  but for Yakut, she let her face down.<br>
