 <br>
When Yakut moved into Hipp's arms, she held the shamaness queen gently.  She could feel the power and weight of Yakut's pain and sorrow.  The shamaness's aura was so intense.  She whispered to her softly, &quot;Yakut, I cannot imagine that you did anything to upset the great mother.  You off all amazons, She surely adores.  Perhaps, Lynn's tasks on this land are finished....and there is something else out there for her.  A new path.&quot;  As she whispered, Hippolyte gently ran her tanned fingers over the back of Yakut's hair, consoling.  It made her almost tremble...feeling the intenseness of Yakut's pain.  Unlike the those trained as shamanesses, Hippolyte was weak to those senses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#6F6F6F>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29>Amazons of the Tanais River Valley</a> <font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href="http://pub163.ezboard.com/bmythicalodysseyforum">Home</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.3m<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

